TiddlyWiki is a Single-Page web browser application. It functions as a Document Editor that supports HTML formatting. It uses Javascript events to enable dynamic loading of content pages called Tiddlers.

                              Application Test Run - Download from Website

                              14th April 2020 at 11:04pm
                              Application Test Run Tutorial

                              In comparison with installing Windows software, a TiddlyWiki application does not get placed on the Start Menu.

                              To download the TiddlyWiki Application

                              1. Use your web browser to go to TiddlyWiki.com
                                _
                              2. In the GettingStarted section, click the button Download Empty

                              3. If the web browser notifies you that "tiddlywiki.com wants to download multiple files", click Allow.

                              4. Use Windows Explorer to go to your Downloads directory. Find the file named empty.html

                              5. Rename the empty.html file

                                Example: Important Notes.html

                              6. Use Windows Explorer to open your new TiddlyWiki application

                              Continue on to Setup a new TiddlyWiki Application

                              Application Test Run - Save your TiddlyWiki Application

                              14th April 2020 at 11:03pm
                              Application Save Application Test Run Tutorial

                              Continued from Application Test Run - Setup a new TiddlyWiki Application

                              1. You can see your new Index tiddler

                              2. In the Sidebar menu, click the Circle-Checkmark

                              3. Close the TiddlyWiki Application's web browser tab
                              4. Use Windows Explorer to go to your Downloads directory. Find the new downloaded version of your TiddlyWiki Application

                                Example: Important Notes (1).html

                              5. Use Windows Explorer to open your new application in the web browser
                              6. The Index tiddler is shown when it opens.

                              7. If you wish, you can use Window Explorer to delete the original version's file, and rename the new version to have the original name. This way any bookmarks or Windows Shortcuts you made will still work.

                                Example: Delete Important Notes.html, then rename Important Notes (1).html as Important Notes.html

                              Continue to Control Panel

                              Application Test Run - Setup a new TiddlyWiki Application

                              14th April 2020 at 11:03pm
                              Application New Application Test Run Tutorial

                              Continued from Application Test Run - Download from Website

                              1. Use Windows Explorer to open your new TiddlyWiki application

                              2. Change the Title and Subtitle

                                Example: Important Notes and Email backup and Journal entries

                              3. Change the Default tiddlers textbox to say Index
                              4. Close the Getting Started page
                              5. On the Sidebar, click the + button to create a new Tiddler page

                              6. Change the Tiddler Title to Index and type some text in the main body textbox

                              7. Click the Checkbox on the top left of the Tiddler page

                              8. You can see your new Index tiddler

                              Continue to Save your TiddlyWiki Application

                              Application Test Run - Use the Control Panel

                              14th April 2020 at 11:03pm
                              Application Test Run Tutorial

                              Continued from Application Test Run - Save your TiddlyWiki Application

                              When setting up the application, you used the GettingStarted page to set the application Title, Subtitle, and Default tiddlers. You can change these settings using the Control Panel.

                              1. Using the Sidebar menu, select the Tools tab and click the Control Panel button.

                              2. On the Control Panel tiddler Info tab Basics sub-tab, you can see the Title, Subtitle, and Default tiddlers that you entered

                              3. You can change these fields at any time. When you close the Control Panel tiddler, the changes are automatically saved.

                              Continue to Create a Journal Entry

                              Content How Used - Journal Tiddler Titles

                              14th April 2020 at 10:47pm
                              Content Date Format How Used Journal Tiddler

                              Continued from Language Reference - Date Format codes

                              See also: Date Format Reference
                              See also: Date Format Design

                              Use the Control Panel tiddler Info tab Basics sub-tab to change the Title of new journal tiddlers. This requires a Date Format code.

                              • The default date pattern is DDth MMM YYYY.

                                Example date result: 11th April 2020

                              • You can add 24-hour time to the end of that date format: DDth MMM YYYY 0hh:0mm:0ss

                                Example date result: 11th April 2020 05:04:36

                              • I prefer to have the date in a Year-Month-Day format: YYYY-0MM-0DD 0hh:0mm:0ss

                                Example date result: 2020-04-11 06:04:46

                              Content Test Run - Create a Journal Entry

                              14th April 2020 at 11:03pm
                              Content Journal Tiddler Test Run Tutorial

                              Continued from Application Test Run - Use the Control Panel

                              See also: Journal Tiddler How Used

                              1. The top-right corner of the Index tiddler has a drop-down menu. Select the new journal here option.

                              2. Please note that the new Journal tiddler has the current date and time for a title, and there are two yellow Tags below the title: Index and Journal

                              3. Enter some data in the body textbox and close the tiddler editor using the Checkmark button.
                              4. Save your TiddlyWiki Application and re-open it. You will not see the new Journal tiddler.
                              5. Using the Sidebar menu, select the More tab Tags sub-tab. You will see both the Inbox tag and the Journal tag.

                              6. Click on one of the tags to see a link to the Journal tiddler.

                              7. The Journal tiddler is shown.

                              Continue to List all Journal Tiddlers

                              Content Test Run - Delete a Tiddler

                              14th April 2020 at 11:02pm
                              Content Test Run Tutorial

                              Continued from Content Test Run - List all Journal Tiddlers

                              One of the Journal tiddlers does not have a time stamp. We can delete this tiddler.

                              1. Click on the Index tiddler list link for the Journal tiddler that does not have a time stamp.

                              2. Use the Journal tiddler drop-down menu to select the Delete option.

                              3. The Journal tiddler is deleted.
                              4. Note: The Index tiddler list automatically updated. It now shows only one Journal tiddler.

                              Content Test Run - List all Journal Tiddlers

                              14th April 2020 at 11:03pm
                              Content Date Format Journal Tiddler List Links Test Run Tutorial

                              Continued from Content Test Run - Create a Journal Entry

                              See also: Date Format How Used
                              See also: Journal Tiddler How Used

                              Instead of using the Sidebar menu More tab Tags sub-tab to see all the Journal tiddlers, you can create a list of all the tiddlers with the Journal tag in the main Index tiddler.

                              1. Use the Pencil button to edit the Index tiddler

                              2. Turn on the Preview tab by clicking the "Closed Eyelid" button.

                              3. Delete all the text in the body textbox.
                              4. Copy the following text and paste it into the body textbox.

                                <<list-links filter:"[tag[Journal]]">>

                                • Please note that the above code is case sensitive. If you type it, all the letters are lower-case except for the capital J in Journal.
                              5. You should see the Journal entry title appear as a blue link in the Preview tab.

                              6. Close the tiddler editor.
                              7. Use the Control Panel tiddler Info tab Basics sub-tab to change the Title of new journal tiddlers: YYYYm0MMd0DD 0hh:0mm:0ss

                                • Please note that the above code is case sensitive.
                              8. Using the drop-down menu of the Index tiddler, select the new journal here option.
                              9. Close the tiddler editor.
                              10. Note: The Index tiddler's list automatically updates to show both Journal tiddler titles.
                              11. Save your TiddlyWiki Application and re-open it. Your Index tiddler shows the list Journal tiddler titles.
                              12. Click on one of the links to show that Journal tiddler.

                              Continue to Delete a Tiddler

                              Language Design - Date Format codes

                              14th April 2020 at 10:48pm
                              Date Format Design Language

                              See also: Date Format Reference

                              The Date Format codes use capital letters for the Date part and lower-case letters for the time part.

                              Example: YYYY-0MM-0DD 0hh:0mm:0ss

                              This makes the time part visually shorter than the date part.

                              Other programs like Microsoft Excel, Microsoft .NET, and others have their own unique ways of identifying 12-hours vs 24-hour times.

                              Language Reference - Date Format codes

                              14th April 2020 at 10:48pm
                              Date Format Language Reference

                              See also: Date Format Design

                              On TiddlyWiki.com, there is a TiddlyWiki Date Format reference

                              _
                              .

                              This can be used in the Journal Tiddler Titles .

                              Examples:

                              • DDth MMM YYYY
                                • DD = the number for day of the month, like 1, 7, 10, 31
                                • th = an ordinal suffix, like 1st, 3rd, 9th
                                • MMM = the spelled-out name of the month
                                • YYYY = the four-digit year
                              • DDth MMM YYYY 0hh:0mm:0ss
                                • DD through YYYY as above
                                • 0hh = the two-digit hour, like 01, 07, 10, 23
                                • : = a literal colon separator
                                • 0mm = the two-digit minute, like 01, 07, 10, 59
                                • 0ss = the two-digit second, like 01, 07, 10, 59
                              • YYYY-0MM-0DD 0hh:0mm:0ss
                                • 0MM = the two-digit month, like 01, 07, 10, 12
                                • 0DD = the two-digit day, like 01, 07, 10, 31

                              A letter can be used as a separator when it does not combine into a specific code.

                              • YYYYm0MMd0DD

                                Example: 2020m04d26

                                • The single m and d characters are not date format codes, so they are treated as literal separators.
